Privacy Policy
ChatOnMac's Services are offered worldwide, the information about you that we process when you use the Services in the EU may be used, stored, and/or accessed by individuals operating outside the European Economic Area (EEA) who work for us, other members of our group of companies, or third-party data processors. This is required for the purposes listed in the
"How and why we use information" section
in this policy.
When providing information about you to entities outside the EEA, we will take appropriate measures to ensure that the recipient protects your personal information adequately in accordance with this Privacy Policy as required by applicable law. These measures include entering into European Commission approved standard contractual arrangements with entities based in countries outside the EEA.
You can ask us for more information about the steps we take to protect your personal information when transferring it from the EU.
Third-Party Software and Services
If you’d like to use other third-party software or services which ChatOnMac tools such as our browser extensions and news/RSS readers allow you to access and interface with as learning resources, please keep in mind that interacting with them may mean providing information about yourself to those third parties. For example, some third-party services may request that you sign up for an account on their platform. Please note that if you use the third-party service or grant access, your data will be handled in accordance with the third party’s privacy policy and practices. We don’t own or control these third parties, and they have their own rules about information collection, use, and sharing, which you should review before using the software or services.
Visitors to our users' shared content
We also process information about visitors to our users’ content on behalf of our users and in accordance with our user agreements.
Users control the content posted on their shared learning resources, so any disputes regarding content on a user’s profile or shared materials should be made directly to the content owner as able, by leaving a comment on their resources, or by contacting ChatOnMac for possible assistance if such means are unavailable.
Account and personal data deletion
An automated account and personal data deletion option is maintained for users at this page: https://ChatOnMac.com/accounts/delete-all-account-data/ - please note that this page requires that users are logged-in to the account they wish to delete. For deletion requests this tool does not cover, please contact us at alex@ChatOnMac.com
Privacy Policy changes
Although most changes are likely to be minor, ChatOnMac may change its Privacy Policy from time to time. ChatOnMac encourages visitors to frequently check this page for any changes to its Privacy Policy. If we make changes, we will notify you by revising the revision log, and, in some cases, we may provide additional notice (like adding a statement to our homepage or sending you a notification through email or in your app). Your further use of the Services after a change to our Privacy Policy will be subject to the updated policy.
